data.title: Music History Events: Releases
data.meta_description: List of events in music history for the category Releases
data.text:
Gladys Knight and the Pips release "I Heard It Through The Grapevine."

The Doors release "People Are Strange."

Arlo Guthrie releases Alice's Restaurant.

The Beach Boys release Smiley Smile, a stripped-down version of their unreleased album Smile that includes "Good Vibrations."

Sam and Dave release "Soul Man."

The Temptations release "You're My Everything."

In America, The Beatles release "All You Need Is Love," John Lennon's maxim. It becomes their 14th #1 hit in that country.

Bobbie Gentry's first single, "Ode To Billie Joe," is released. It would go on to top the Hot 100 for four weeks.

The Hollies release "Carrie Anne."

Moby Grape release all five singles from their debut album: "Changes," "Sitting By The Window," "8:05," "Omaha," and "Hey Grandma."

Stevie Wonder releases "I Was Made To Love Her."

David Bowie releases his self-titled debut album, David Bowie, which bares little resemblance to his future work.

The Beatles release their landmark album Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band in the UK.More

Procol Harum release "A Whiter Shade Of Pale."

Elvis Presley releases Easy Come, Easy Go.

Jimi Hendrix releases "Purple Haze" in the UK.

The Velvet Underground releases The Velvet Underground And Nico.

The Beatles release "Strawberry Fields Forever" as a single in the US, with "Penny Lane" on the flip side.

The Rolling Stones release their album Between The Buttons in America, with "Let's Spend the Night Together" and "Ruby Tuesday" on the track list.

The Turtles release "Happy Together."

The Electric Prunes release "I Had Too Much To Dream Last Night."

Donovan releases "Mellow Yellow."

The Zombies release "She's Not There" in the US.

The Association release "Cherish."

The Monkees release their first single, "Last Train To Clarksville." It's a lighthearted-sounding song with a somber subtext: The lyric is about a guy who gets drafted into the Vietnam War and wonders if he's ever coming home.

The Beatles release Revolver, which contains the psychedelic "Tomorrow Never Knows" and the bitter "Taxman."

The Beatles release "Eleanor Rigby" on a double A-side single with "Yellow Submarine."

The Temptations release "Beauty Is Only Skin Deep."

The Supremes release "You Can't Hurry Love."

The Lovin' Spoonful release "Summer In The City."
